<h1 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center" style="font-size:60px;line-height:1.2">Sliders</h1>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The <strong>Sliders</strong> page offers a diverse collection of customizable slider components designed to bring motion and visual interest to your website. From classic carousels to elegant fade transitions and interactive coverflow effects, each slider is built for both form and function. Effects like <strong>fade, coverflow, and progress indicators</strong> are available across two main block types: the <strong>Slider block</strong> and the <strong>Image Gallery block</strong>. </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The <strong>Slider block</strong> uses flexible content patterns to generate slide layouts—ideal for showcasing text, products, or testimonials—while the <strong>Image Gallery block</strong> lets you load images directly into the editor for quick visual setups. With options for <strong>autoplay, looped playback, arrow or dot navigation</strong>, and top-mounted progress bars, these sliders adapt to a wide range of content and use cases.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Additional styles not available in the block settings can be added using WordPress's built-in CSS editor.</p>
